<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-10-25T17:05:25-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-10-25T17:05:25-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51695#p51695</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51695#p51695"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[How to choose palette and attribute table data?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51695#p51695"><![CDATA[
The most common code for black is $0F. The color code $0D actually outputs a <em>negative</em> lightness value that a few TVs have problems with.<br /><br />Here's a <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Samurai-Pizza-Cats/dp/B0006L1PDY" class="postlink">3-color logo</a> that might pose fewer problems. The shuriken could be a sprite.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Oct 25, 2009 5:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
