<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51681#p51681</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51681#p51681"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[How to choose palette and attribute table data?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5672&amp;p=51681#p51681"><![CDATA[
Each background palette line will take the form:<br />0=background<br />1=black outline<br />2=one color<br />3=another color<br /><br />The opening credits spell it "SAM/UR/I", showing one syllable at once, but the <a href="http://www.toonjunkie.com/product.php?productid=17061&amp;cat=0&amp;page=1&amp;gclid=CLSSyf6J2Z0CFQ4MDQodsXYksg" class="postlink">DVD box</a> spells it "SAMURAI". As far as I can tell, it's "SAMURAI" when written on one line and "SAM/UR/I" when each syllable fills the screen. But the logo resembles that of Super Mario Bros. 3 and might not even need colors per letter to look good.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Oct 25, 2009 1:58 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
